    think='Now let me fix Minor #4 - EmptyRecommendationView fallback to BLoC. I
need to:\n1. Add `EmptyStateFallbackRequested` event to matching_event.dart\n2. 
Handle it in MatchingBloc with smart fallback strategy\n3. Update HomePage to di
spatch this event instead of hardcoding \'nationwide\'\n\nThe fallback strategy 
according to the review: "由 BLoC 根据当前 mode 决定 fallback 策略". Looking at 
the design spec reference, it says if user is in city mode and sees empty state,
clicking the button should fall back. A sensible strategy would be:\n- `nearby` 
-> `nationwide`\n- `city` -> `nationwide` (or could be `nearby` then `nationwide
`, but let\'s keep it simple)\n- `nationwide` -> no button shown (already the ca
se)\n\nActually, looking at EmptyRecommendationView, it only shows the button wh
en `mode != \'nationwide\'`. So the fallback from `city` could go to `nearby` fi
rst, then `nationwide`. But let me look at the review again: "将 onChangeMode 的
行为提升到 MatchingBloc 层，由 BLoC 根据当前 mode 决定 fallback 策略，page 层仅
透传事件。"\n\nA simple strategy:\n- If current mode is `nearby`, fallback to `n
ationwide`\n- If current mode is `city`, fallback to `nationwide` (or `nearby` -
> `nationwide`)\n\nI\'ll implement:\n- `city` -> `nearby`\n- `nearby` -> `nation
wide`\n\nWait, looking at the current HomePage code:\n```dart\nif (state is Matc
hingLoadEmpty) {\n  return EmptyRecommendationView(\n    mode: state.mode,\n    
onChangeMode: () {\n      context.read<MatchingBloc>().add(\n        const Recom
mendationsRequested(mode: \'nationwide\'),\n      );\n    },\n  );\n}\n```\n\nTh
e user currently sees "切换全国" button. If they\'re in `city` mode, clicking it
jumps to `nationwide`. The review says "如果未来需要更智能的 fallback（如 city 
空时先尝试 nearby），当前写死逻辑会阻碍扩展。"\n\nSo the fix is to make it exten
sible. Let me create an event that the BLoC handles.\n\nActually, wait. Let me r
e-read the review more carefully:\n"修复: 将 onChangeMode 的行为提升到 MatchingB
loc 层，由 BLoC 根据当前 mode 决定 fallback 策略，page 层仅透传事件。"\n\nSo I n
eed:\n1. New event `EmptyStateFallbackRequested` (no parameters needed, BLoC kno
ws current mode)\n2. In BLoC handler, look at current state\'s mode and decide n
ext mode\n3. Page just emits the event\n\nFor the fallback strategy, let me thin
k:\n- If mode is `city`, fallback to `nearby` (closer first) or `nationwide`?\n-
If mode is `nearby`, fallback to `nationwide`\n\nThe PRD says the modes are `nea
rby`, `city`, `nationwide`. A reasonable cascade:\n- `city` -> `nearby` -> `nati
onwide`\nBut wait, `city` is supposed to be smaller than `nearby`? No, looking a
t the current implementation, both are 50km. But conceptually, `city` should be 
city boundary (smaller), `nearby` is 50km (larger). So:\n- `city` empty -> try `
nearby`\n- `nearby` empty -> try `nationwide`\n\nActually, looking at the existi
ng behavior, it always goes to `nationwide`. Let me implement a simple strategy 
that matches the current behavior but is extensible:\n- `city` -> `nationwide`\n
- `nearby` -> `nationwide`\n\nBut to be more extensible as the review suggests:\
n- `city` -> `nearby`\n- `nearby` -> `nationwide`\n\nHmm, but if `city` and `nea
rby` are both 50km in current implementation, going from `city` to `nearby` won\
't help. Let me just do what makes sense conceptually:\n- `city` -> `nearby` (fa
llback to wider radius)\n- `nearby` -> `nationwide` (fallback to no radius limit
)\n\nWait, I should check if the design spec says anything. The review cites `de
signs/issue-4/design-spec.md` 第 147 行. Let me check that file.',
